{
  "stem": "3631.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was very much tempted to-- to write to Thomas Keneally, the author of the book, to be-- to give him my-- my input.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then, I was afraid-- I didn't talk about it at all.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was afraid, again, what-- what would it do to my life?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I-- I-- I let it go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when the book was published, I bought a few copies of it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I sent to to all-- to-- to friends of ours, [INAUDIBLE] to-- to Martha's family, and so on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- I put a little inscription in it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I may-- I'll read this for you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Here's what I wrote.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was in 1982. 'Dear friend, this true story of Oskar Schindler's author in frightening detail the story of my-- my parents and my sister's life between 1939 and May, 1945 in Krakow, the ghetto in Krakow, Podgorze, the concentration camps in Krakow, Plaszow, Gross-Rosen, and Auschwitz, and Schindler's labor camp in Brinnlitz, Czechoslovakia, from which we were liberated by the Russians on May 9, 1945.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew most characters in the book-- Germans and Jews-- personally.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I knew every street and place.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We lived there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were in every happening and action related in the book.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Reading this book brought back many painful memories of names and events long forgotten.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it made me realize the absolute miracle of our reunification and survival in Brinnlitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I want the people close to me to have this book.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I urge you and, if possible, your children to read it for three reasons.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Number one, a selfish one, for me.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
